FBIS3-39067 "drweu028_q_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 TURKEY Bosnia Intervention Seen as Test of Friendship TA0902194294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 GMT 9 Feb 94 TA0902194294 Ankara TRT Television Network Language: Turkish Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Addressing a ground-breaking ceremony in Izmir, Murat Karayalcin, state minister and deputy prime minister, said that in the wake of the latest Serbian attack in Bosnia-Herzegovina, Turkey made requests in NATO for an intervention. He added: [Begin Karayalcin recording] Those who are our friends, those who are our allies, if they want to continue with their friendship and alliance with Turkey, this is their chance. They must take it. They must decide to intervene on the Serbian artillery positions in the hills around Sarajevo. They must end this massacre. Turkey will assess this. It might assess it today or in the future. If Turkey's friendship, the Turkish people's friendship, is important for the Western forces, they have an opportunity to show it. Let them show their friendship. In turn, we will show our friendship. From now on, we will display this determined stand regarding Bosnia-Herzegovina. [end recording] [passage omitted]
